{"id": 2486, "source": "pestle", "subject": "physics", "course": null, "level": "HL", "paper": "1", "year": "2018", "session": "18M", "subtopic": "12-1-the-interaction-of-matter-with-radiation", "title": "18M.1.HL.TZ1.37", "topic_id": "12", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>Two radioactive nuclides, X and Y, have half-lives of 50 s and 100 s respectively. At time <em>t </em>= 0 samples of X and Y contain the same number of nuclei.</p>\n<p>What is <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{number of nuclei of X undecayed}}}}{{{\\text{number of nuclei of Y undecayed}}}}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>number of nuclei of X undecayed</mtext>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mrow>\n<mtext>number of nuclei of Y undecayed</mtext>\n</mrow>\n</mrow>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span> when <em>t </em>= 200 s?</p>\n<p>A.     4</p>\n<p>B.     2</p>\n<p>C.     <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{1}{2}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mn>1</mn>\n<mn>2</mn>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>D.     <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{1}{4}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n<mfrac>\n<mn>1</mn>\n<mn>4</mn>\n</mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>D</p>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n[N/A]\n</div>"}